<%= render 'shared/navbar' %>
<div class="languages-container">
  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1440 320">
    <path fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" d="M0,160L48,154.7C96,149,192,139,288,138.7C384,139,480,149,576,133.3C672,117,768,75,864,90.7C960,107,1056,181,1152,192C1248,203,1344,149,1392,122.7L1440,96L1440,0L1392,0C1344,0,1248,0,1152,0C1056,0,960,0,864,0C768,0,672,0,576,0C480,0,384,0,288,0C192,0,96,0,48,0L0,0Z"></path>
  </svg>
    <div class="main-container-language">
      <h2> <%= @language.name %></h2>
        <div class="card-description">
          <p>The HyperText Markup Language, or HTML is the standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. It can be assisted by technologies such as Cascading Style Sheets and scripting languages such as JavaScript.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  <div class="main-container-courses">
  
      <%@language.courses.each do|course|%>
      <div class="card-course">
      <img src="<%= image_path("man-coding.jpg")  %>">
        <h4> <%= link_to course.name, course_path(course) %> </h4>
        <div class="card-text-course ">
        <p>Take the first step towards a career in design or development and read our intro on HTML. Learn why HTML is one of the most relevant & widely used programming languages today.</p>
        </div>
        <h5> <i class="fas fa-dollar-sign"> </i> 30.99 </h5>
        <h5> <i class="fas fa-tachometer-alt"> </i> <%= course.description %> </h5>
        
      <%end%>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>